      "content": "The notion of a permanent underclass is a dire consequence of unchecked government expansion, and it is a very real possibility under current trends. Excessive state intervention fundamentally alters individual responsibility, creating a culture of dependency rather than self-reliance. If the state becomes the primary provider for every citizen, the natural drive for productive labor erodes, leading to a permanently subsidized segment of the population.",
      "source": "target",
